<bill id="DLM2965200" in.amend="false" irdnumbering="no" official="yes" xml:lang="en-NZ" year.imprint="2010" bill.no="154" bill.type="local" stage="1" year="2010">
  <billdetail>
    <title>Hamilton City Council (Parana Park) Land Vesting Bill</title>
    <billtype>Local Bill</billtype>
    <explnote id="DLM2965201" in.amend="false" irdnumbering="no" official="yes" rule-after="yes" rule-before="yes" bill.no="154" bill.type="local" stage="1" year="2010">
      <heading>Explanatory note</heading>
      <explnote.group>
        <heading>General policy statement</heading>
        <para>
          <text>The purpose of this Bill is to vest Lots 1, 2, and 3 DPS 3401 (called Parana Park) in the Hamilton City Council as a recreation reserve subject to the provisions of the Reserves Act 1977.</text>
        </para>
        <para>
          <text>George Parr of Hamilton, farmer, died on or about the 26th day of February 1929 and by his last Will, probate of which was granted to the Public Trustee, gifted his freehold property situated at number 3 River Road, Hamilton, being Lots 1, 2, and 3 DPS 3401, to the Mayor, Councillors, and Burgesses of the Borough of Hamilton to be used as follows:</text>
          <list>
            <item>
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
              <para>
                <text>as to the dwelling house situated on Lot 1 DPS 3401, together with such amount of land as the Hamilton Borough Council for the time being shall think necessary, for a children’s convalescent home for patients from the Waikato Hospital; and</text>
              </para>
            </item>
            <item>
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
              <para>
                <text>as to the remainder of the land comprised in the said freehold property for a children’s playground, to be known as Parana Park.</text>
              </para>
            </item>
          </list>
        </para>
        <para>
          <text>In the 1950s it became apparent that the dwelling house situated on Lot 1 DPS 3401 was most unsuitable for a children’s convalescent home and in 1958 the Hamilton City (Parana Park) Empowering Act 1958 was passed to enable the Hamilton City Council to more effectively administer and manage Parana Park.</text>
        </para>
        <para>
          <text>Parana Park is currently used for passive recreation activities and the Hamilton City Council considers it appropriate to update and modernise the legislation by which it holds Parana Park by promoting a local Bill to vest Parana Park in the Hamilton City Council as a recreation reserve subject to the provisions of the Reserves Act 1977.</text>
        </para>
      </explnote.group>
      <explnote.group>
        <heading>Clause by clause analysis</heading>
        <clause.desc>
          <para>
            <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 1</emphasis> is the Title clause.</text>
          </para>
        </clause.desc>
        <clause.desc>
          <para>
            <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 2</emphasis> is the commencement clause and provides for the Bill to come into force on the day after the date on which it receives the Royal assent.</text>
          </para>
        </clause.desc>
        <clause.desc>
          <para>
            <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 3</emphasis> defines terms used in the Bill.</text>
          </para>
        </clause.desc>
        <clause.desc>
          <para>
            <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 4</emphasis> sets out the purpose of the Bill.</text>
          </para>
        </clause.desc>
        <clause.desc>
          <para>
            <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 5</emphasis> vests Lots 1, 2, and 3 DPS 3401 in Hamilton City Council, and frees the land from the trusts of the Last Will and Testament of George Parr and from the conditions imposed by the Hamilton City (Parana Park) Empowering Act 1958.</text>
          </para>
        </clause.desc>
        <clause.desc>
          <para>
            <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 6</emphasis> requires the Hamilton City Council to hold Lots 1, 2, and 3 DPS 3401 as a recreation reserve subject to the provisions of the Reserves Act 1977.</text>
          </para>
        </clause.desc>
        <clause.desc>
          <para>
            <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 7</emphasis> gives the Hamilton City Council with respect to Lots 1, 2, and 3 DPS 3401 the powers as set out in the Reserves Act 1977.</text>
          </para>
        </clause.desc>
        <clause.desc>
          <para>
            <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 8</emphasis> provides that, to avoid doubt, the vesting of the land and property is not subject to the Estate and Gift Duties Act 1968, the Goods and Services Tax Act 1985, or the Income Tax Act 2007.</text>
          </para>
        </clause.desc>
        <clause.desc>
          <para>
            <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 9</emphasis> authorises the Registrar-General of Land to make such entries in the Land Transfer registers as are necessary to give effect to the Bill.</text>
          </para>
        </clause.desc>
        <clause.desc>
          <para>
            <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 10</emphasis> repeals the Hamilton City (Parana Park) Empowering Act 1958.</text>
          </para>
        </clause.desc>
      </explnote.group>
    </explnote>
  </billdetail>
